From 10be656e73b2386e7189dbf9942485885dad3d97 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: psyclyx <me@psyclyx.xyz>
Date: Fri, 3 Apr 2026 08:28:28 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] feat: add wl_drm protocol for Mesa EGL GPU device discovery

Mesa's EGL Wayland platform uses the wl_drm protocol to discover which
DRM render node to open for GPU-accelerated rendering. Without this,
eglInitialize() fails because it cannot find a GPU device.

The implementation:
- Advertises /dev/dri/renderD128 as the DRM device
- Sends supported pixel formats and PRIME capability
- Handles authenticate as a no-op (render nodes skip DRM auth)
- Rejects create_buffer/create_prime_buffer (clients use linux-dmabuf)

This enables EGL initialization for chroot Wayland clients (e.g. GTK4
apps running in Arch Linux ARM) that need hardware-accelerated GL via
Mesa's Freedreno/kgsl Gallium driver.

Change-Id: I9712a39e669e30528f212c062c2604b36643aa66
